{
  "texts": [
    "CNNs are pivotal in high-level and multi-scale feature representation within salient object detection.",
    "These architectures have proven effective in various computer vision tasks, including edge detection, object recognition, and semantic segmentation.",
    "Eleonora (Vig et al., 2014) pioneered a data-driven approach, leveraging deep networks with diverse layers and parameters to maximize feature extraction.",
    "Similarly, Kümmerer et al. (2014) introduced Deep Gaze, which utilized AlexNet to create a high-dimensional feature space for saliency mapping, addressing challenges posed by limited training data.",
    "Extending this idea, Huang et al. (2015) fine-tuned pre-trained object recognition deep networks using saliency evaluation metrics such as Similarity and KL-Divergence."
  ]
}